chunks.text: ## MAXIMO SELF-PACED TRAINING GUIDE ## INFORMATION TECHNOLOGY ASSET ASSIGNER ## Asset Assigner Role in Maximo In Maximo, the Asset Assigner assigns Assets such as Government Furnished Equipment (GFE) to individual staff members at their site. Upon return of the Asset, the Asset Assigner ends the assignment. ## Available Training Resources EAWM Maximo Training Page to help users learn their role and responsibilities in Maximo at their own pace and in a mode that best fits their learning style. - · User Guides provide the greatest amount of detail on each topic. User Guides include a high-level summary, detailed step-by-step instructions with screen captures, and a Business Process Model mapping out the activities performed by each affected Functional Community. User Guides can be found in the 'Training Materials by Role' section of the Training page, under via links to the Functional Community and Role name. - · Job Aids target critical functionality in Maximo.

r Guides can be found in the 'Training Materials by Role' section of the Training page, under via links to the Functional Community and Role name. - · Job Aids target critical functionality in Maximo. These documents are intended to be brief and focus on key issues, highlighting essential steps. These are found in the 'User Documentation' section of the Training page. - · Quick Reference Documents (QRDs) include step-by-step work instructions, in simplest terms. Unlike Job Aids and User Guides, QRDs normally do not include screen captures. These are also posted in the 'User Documentation' section. - · Video Demonstrations allow playback of recorded sessions narrated by Instructors, walking through the steps of completing a given task in Maximo. In addition to the items available on the Training page, this Self-Paced Training Guide directs you to short video demonstrations recorded and narrated by Maximo Instructors as they walk through the steps of completing specific tasks in Maximo.

aining page, this Self-Paced Training Guide directs you to short video demonstrations recorded and narrated by Maximo Instructors as they walk through the steps of completing specific tasks in Maximo. To train for your role, read the appropriate User Guide, Job Aid and/or QRD for a given topic to gain an understanding of the process. Also, watch the video demonstrations as noted below. Continue reviewing this information until you are ready to start working in Maximo. IMPORTANT! Please DO NOT attempt to practice any of the steps in the Maximo Production system. If, after reviewing the materials, you are still uncomfortable with working in Maximo, contact your Maximo Site Lead for additional guidance. ## MAXIMO SELF-PACED TRAINING GUIDE ## Assign Assets - End Asset Assignments The Asset Assigner assigns Assets (GFE) to individual staff members and ends Asset assignment once returned in Maximo. The Borrower (who the Asset is assigned to) electronically signs for their assigned Assets and

igner assigns Assets (GFE) to individual staff members and ends Asset assignment once returned in Maximo. The Borrower (who the Asset is assigned to) electronically signs for their assigned Assets and recertifies for the Asset annually (every 60 days for contractors). - · To read the User Guide on this topic, please go to the Information Technology Asset Management Training Materials page; under the Asset Assigner tab, select the Check Out Asset User Guide to download the file - · To see demonstrations of using Maximo, please go to EAWM Maximo Video Demos. Under the section, Information Technology (IT) , locate the videos for the role Asset Assigner . The following videos pertain to this topic (please note that the videos will launch in a separate media player): - o Assign Asset to Borrower - Assigner - o Print VA Property Pass - Borrower - o Recertify Asset - Borrower - o End Asset Assignment - Assigner
